\title{Zls Integration}

\taxon{skill}

\meta{version}{1.0.0}

\meta{trit}{0}

\meta{description}{"zls-integration skill"}

\subtree{
\title{ZLS Integration Skill}
\p{Zig Language Server (ZLS) provides IDE features for Zig development. This skill covers installation, configuration, build-on-save diagnostics, and troubleshooting.}

\subtree{
\title{Quick Reference}
\pre{\startverb
| Feature | ZLS Support | Notes |
|---------|-------------|-------|
| Autocomplete | ✓ Full | Includes comptime-aware completion |
| Goto Definition | ✓ Full | Cross-file navigation |
| Find References | ✓ Full | All usages in workspace |
| Hover Documentation | ✓ Full | Inline docs from source |
| Diagnostics | ⚡ Parser-level | Semantic via build-on-save |
| Rename Symbol | ✓ Full | Safe refactoring |
| Code Actions | ✓ Partial | Fix imports, remove unused |
| Formatting | ✓ Full | Uses `zig fmt` |
\stopverb}
}

\subtree{
\title{Installation}
\subtree{
\title{Via Package Manager (Recommended)}
\pre{\startverb
# macOS (Homebrew)
brew install zls

# Nix/Flox
flox install zls

# Arch Linux
pacman -S zls

# From source (any platform)
git clone https://github.com/zigtools/zls
cd zls
zig build -Doptimize=ReleaseSafe
\stopverb}
}

\subtree{
\title{Version Compatibility}
\pre{\startverb
| Zig Version | ZLS Version | Notes |
|-------------|-------------|-------|
| 0.15.x | 0.15.x | Current stable |
| 0.14.x | 0.14.x | Previous stable |
| 0.13.x | 0.13.x | Legacy |
| master | master | Build from source |
\stopverb}

\p{\strong{Always match ZLS version to Zig version.}}
}
}

\subtree{
\title{Configuration}
\subtree{
\title{zls.json Location}
\pre{\startverb
~/.config/zls.json           # Linux/macOS
%APPDATA%\zls.json           # Windows
<project>/.zls.json          # Project-specific
\stopverb}
}

\subtree{
\title{Essential Configuration}
\pre{\startverb
{
  "zig_exe_path": "/path/to/zig",
  "enable_autofix": true,
  "enable_import_access": true,
  "highlight_global_var_declarations": true,
  "warn_style": true,
  "enable_build_on_save": true,
  "build_on_save_step": "check"
}
\stopverb}
}
}

\subtree{
\title{Build-On-Save Diagnostics}
\p{ZLS can run your build script on save to catch semantic errors (type mismatches, wrong argument counts) that parser-level analysis misses.}

\subtree{
\title{Step 1: Add Check Step to build.zig}
\pre{\startverb
// build.zig
pub fn build(b: *std.Build) void {
    const target = b.standardTargetOptions(.{});
    const optimize = b.standardOptimizeOption(.{});

    const exe = b.addExecutable(.{
        .name = "myapp",
        .root_source_file = b.path("src/main.zig"),
        .target = target,
        .optimize = optimize,
    });
    b.installArtifact(exe);

    // ZLS check step - runs on save
    const check = b.addExecutable(.{
        .name = "myapp",
        .root_source_file = b.path("src/main.zig"),
        .target = target,
        .optimize = optimize,
    });
    
    const check_step = b.step("check", "Check compilation (for ZLS)");
    check_step.dependOn(&check.step);
}
\stopverb}
}

\subtree{
\title{Step 2: Configure ZLS}
\pre{\startverb
{
  "enable_build_on_save": true,
  "build_on_save_step": "check"
}
\stopverb}
}

\subtree{
\title{Step 3: Editor Setup}
\p{\strong{VS Code (zls extension):}}

\pre{\startverb
// settings.json
{
  "zig.zls.path": "/path/to/zls",
  "zig.zls.enableBuildOnSave": true
}
\stopverb}

\p{\strong{Neovim (nvim-lspconfig):}}

\pre{\startverb
require('lspconfig').zls.setup({
  settings = {
    zls = {
      enable_build_on_save = true,
      build_on_save_step = "check"
    }
  }
})
\stopverb}

\p{\strong{Emacs (lsp-mode):}}

\pre{\startverb
(setq lsp-zig-zls-executable "/path/to/zls")
(setq lsp-zig-enable-build-on-save t)
\stopverb}
}
}

\subtree{
\title{Troubleshooting}
\subtree{
\title{No Diagnostics Appearing}
\ol{
\li{Verify ZLS is running: \code{\startverb pgrep -l zls\stopverb}}
\li{Check ZLS log: \code{\startverb ~/.cache/zls/zls.log\stopverb}}
\li{Ensure Zig version matches: \code{\startverb zig version\stopverb} vs \code{\startverb zls --version\stopverb}}
\li{Test build manually: \code{\startverb zig build check\stopverb}}
}
}

\subtree{
\title{Slow Completions}
\pre{\startverb
{
  "skip_std_references": true,
  "prefer_ast_check_as_child_process": true
}
\stopverb}
}

\subtree{
\title{Import Resolution Failures}
\pre{\startverb
{
  "enable_import_access": true,
  "additional_module_paths": ["deps/", "vendor/"]
}
\stopverb}
}

\subtree{
\title{Build-On-Save Not Working}
\ol{
\li{Verify \code{\startverb check\stopverb} step exists in build.zig}
\li{Run \code{\startverb zig build check\stopverb} manually}
\li{Check ZLS config: \code{\startverb enable_build_on_save: true\stopverb}}
\li{Restart language server}
}
}
}

\subtree{
\title{GF(3) Integration}
\p{ZLS diagnostics map to triadic workflow:}

\pre{\startverb
| Diagnostic Type | Trit | Action |
|-----------------|------|--------|
| Error (red) | -1 | Must fix before build |
| Warning (yellow) | 0 | Review, may ignore |
| Hint (blue) | +1 | Optimization opportunity |
\stopverb}

\p{Conservation: \code{\startverb errors + warnings + hints → 0\stopverb} as code improves.}
}

\subtree{
\title{Editor Integration Matrix}
\pre{\startverb
| Editor | Plugin | Config Path |
|--------|--------|-------------|
| VS Code | zls (extension) | `.vscode/settings.json` |
| Neovim | nvim-lspconfig | `init.lua` or `lsp.lua` |
| Helix | Built-in | `languages.toml` |
| Emacs | lsp-mode + lsp-zig | `init.el` |
| Sublime | LSP-zig | `*.sublime-settings` |
| Vim | vim-lsp or coc.nvim | `.vimrc` or `coc-settings.json` |
\stopverb}
}

